observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management direct the: 

GSO to - 
Ensure that critical information necessary for effective management and tracking of PPEs are indicated both in the property ledgers and in the RPCPPE;
Investigate the equipment that cannot be located and make liable the person accountable for the property in case of negligence.

OCA to - 
draw adjusting entries to correct the noted errors in the PPE accounts ;
transfer all public infrastructure assets carried in the Registry of Public Infrastructure in the books of accounts, effect the corresponding depreciation and make necessary disclosures in the Notes to Financial Statements;
OCA and GSO to address the complete reconciliation of books and RPCPPE by installing a system by which- the PPE items recorded by the OCA and the GSO are reconciled regularly;
City Engineer to provide  OCA and GSO with a complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
Strictly comply with Section 111 of PD No. 1445, Section 53, Chapter III of the GAAM, Vol. III, Sections 10 and 13, Chapter 1 of MNGAS for LGUs, Vol.  II, Paragraph 3.7 of COA Circular No. 2016-004 dated September 30, 2016, and COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015.

We recommended that Management direct the accountant to:

Exert effort in locating or producing the documents to support the legitimacy of the dormant account balances;
Pursue action to drop the balances from the books of accounts under COA Circular No. 97-001 in case of balances that could no longer be documented, and accountability thereof could not be established;
Review and analyze the payable accounts to determine the validity of accounts and revert those long outstanding payables to the unappropriated surplus; and
Implement a time-bounded program of eliminating the dormant accounts following state accounting and auditing policies and procedures.

We recommended that Management require:

The Office of the City Accountant (OCA) to perform procedures to identify the lump-sum beginning balances reported in the books and record the necessary adjustments to correct the same and facilitate further reconciliation of balances between the accounting and GSO records;
Subsequently perform reconciliation of the balances reported in the accounting records against the balances reported in the RPCPPE, identify the discrepancies and record the necessary adjustments thereon to arrive at a fairly presented balance in the financial statement.
